Meeting 1.1 – Project Kick-off
Date: 02 March 2026
Time: 10:00 – 10:30
Attendees: All Members
Agenda:
Introduce project concept
Define system objectives and scope
Discussion:
The project idea of developing a Car Hire Management System was introduced and discussed. The main objective identified was to create a system capable of efficiently storing and retrieving car data. Various approaches for data handling were considered, and the need for an efficient search mechanism was highlighted. After discussion, the Binary Search Tree (BST) was proposed as the core data structure due to its ability to perform faster searches compared to linear structures.
Outcome:
Project scope and objectives clearly defined
Decision made to use BST for data storage and searching
